OL,6,FThe daughter of a Londoner who died
OL,7,Ffrom Hepatitis C has spoken of her
OL,8,Fanger after hearing the findings of
OL,9,Fthe inquiry into the infected blood
OL,10,Fscandal.
OL,12,FRosadean Dore, who came to Britain
OL,13,Ffrom her native St Kitts in the
OL,14,FCaribbean to work as a nurse, died in
OL,15,F1997.
OL,17,FHer daughter Annette gave evidence to
OL,18,Fthe inquiry. Mrs Dean is believed to
OL,19,Fhave been infected when she was given
OL,20,Fblood transfusions during childbirth.
