OL,6,FA highly critical inquiry found the
OL,7,Finfected blood scandal "could largely
OL,8,Fhave been avoided" and there was a
OL,9,F"pervasive" cover-up to hide the truth.
OL,11,FDeliberate attempts were made to
OL,12,Fconceal the disaster, including
OL,13,Fevidence of Whitehall officials
OL,14,Fdestroying documents, the Infected
OL,15,FBlood Inquiry found.
OL,17,FPatients were knowingly exposed to
OL,18,Funacceptable risks of infection, the
OL,19,Fprobe found.
